# Issue starting 'Start SOS' - app does not recognize display :2 with secondary display plugged into the dedicated projector graphics card

(Step 1: ) Find the BusID of the secondary GPU (M4000)
lspci | grep -i vga

(Step 2: ) Modify the xorg.conf 
sudo nano /etc/X11/xorg.conf

(2a: ) Replace the ServerLayout section

Section "ServerLayout"
    Identifier     "Layout"
    Screen      0  "Screen0" 0 0
    Screen      1  "Screen1" RightOf "Screen0" #<-- Only added line
    InputDevice    "Keyboard" "CoreKeyboard"
    InputDevice    "Mouse" "CorePointer"
EndSection

(2b: ) Add new sections to the bottom of file
Section "Monitor"
    Identifier     "Monitor1"
    HorizSync       30.0 - 83.0
    VertRefresh     56.0 - 76.0
EndSection

Section "Device"
    Identifier     "Device1"
    Driver         "nvidia"
    VendorName     "NVIDIA Corporation"
    BoardName      "Quadro M4000"
    BusID          "PCI:3:0:0"
    Option         "NoLogo" "1"
    Option         "ProbeAllGpus" "false"
EndSection

Section "Screen"
    Identifier     "Screen1"
    Device         "Device1"
    Monitor        "Monitor1"
    DefaultDepth    24
    SubSection "Display"
        Depth       24
    EndSubSection
EndSection

(Step 3: ) Restart display manager
**Warning** Save any files before running command, user will be logged out and all software automatically closed
sudo systemctl restart display-manager

        Depth       24
